  "body": "Hello community,\r\n\r\nI'm getting around the EIP1155 token ID substitution in the metadata URL.\r\nMaybe it's already feasible, and I missed something, but having the `_uri` declared as `private` to the ERC1155 class makes it impossible to access from potential child classes:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    // Used as the URI for all token types by relying on ID substitution, e.g., https://token-cdn-domain/{id}.json\r\n    string private _uri;\r\n``` \r\n\r\nCould we set it to `internal` instead to be able to override the `uri` function like I'm trying to [here](https://github.com/factchain/factchain-community/pull/67/files) - in the FactChainSFT contract?\r\n \r\nPardon me if it's already feasible or considered a bad practice. \r\n\r\nThanks a lot!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
