    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Hello @Haypierre \r\n\r\nThe URI in the core ERC1155 is initally defined during construction. The uri value can be accessed internally or externally through the `uri(0)` function (or any other id). It can also be updated (internally) using the `_setURI` function.\r\n\r\nIf you want more granular control, you can override the `uri(uint256)` function, has shown in the `ERC1155URIStorage` extension.\r\n\r\nAlso: making variables private good against our guidelines (for many reasons), and should not be necessary here anyway.",
